TY  - JOUR
AU  - Grether, David M.
T1  - Bayes Rule as a Descriptive Model: The Representativeness Heuristic*
PY  - 1980
Y1  - 1980/11/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885092
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 95
IS  - 3
SP  - 537
EP  - 557
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - Results of experiments designed to test the claim of psychologists that expected utility theory does not provide a good descriptive model are reported. The deviation from tested theory is that, in revising beliefs, individuals ignore prior or base-rate information contrary to Bayes rule. Flaws in the evidence in the psychological literature are noted, an experiment avoiding these difficulties is designed and carried out, and the psychologists' predictions are stated in terms of a more general model. The psychologists' predictions are confirmed for inexperienced or financially unmotivated subjects, but for others the evidence is less clear.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1885092
ER  - 



